 `Recent findings:`, `Open questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 2: you have used 115 actions; a strong score needs about 58 or fewer. You are 2.0x over the target.\nIf you are not steadily making progress toward the level goal, commit to your single best hypothesis and the shortest sequence that tests it \u2014 do not exhaustively scan rows/columns or enumerate every option. Test one idea, read the result, then decide.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "KEY DISCOVERY! Clicking on the CHARCOAL block changed the red block's position!\nBefore: R at (20,20)-(23,39)\nAfter: R at (16,28)-(19,39)\nSo the MOUSE action on different targets creates/moves the red block to different positions:\n- Click magenta: red block at (20,20)-(23,39)\n- Click charcoal: red block at (16,28)-(19,39)\nThe new red block at (16,28)-(19,39) is at the same rows as the original red block (16,8)-(19,19) but at cols 28-39, which aligns with the MIDDLE YELLOW ARCH at (4,28)-(11,39)!\nSo the red block is now at (16,28)-(19,39), directly below the middle arch. The blue is at (20,20)-(23,39).\nNow, what's the goal? Maybe:\n1. Move the blue to align with the red block and the arch.\n2. The red block at (16,28)-(19,39) is the \"target\" position for the blue.\n3. Move the blue to (16,28)-(19,39) and SPACE.\nBut the blue is at (20,20)-(23,39). To move to (16,28)-(19,39):\n- UP 1: blue to (16,20)-(19,39). But red at (16,28)-(19,39) is in 